SIMPLE: worsen
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worsen
<hw>Wors"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
worse; to deteriorate; to impair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is apparent that, in the particular point of which we have been
conversing, their condition is greatly <qex>worsened</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To get the better of; to worst.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worsen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Worsen
<hw>Wors"en</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To grow or become worse.</def>
<rj><au>De Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Indifferent health, which seemed rather to <qex>worsen</qex> than
improve.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worser</ent>⟦br⟧
